quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,70,"They said, "
  2,71,"He said, "
  2,72,"And [recall] when you slew a man and disputed{1} over it, but Allāh was to bring out that which you were concealing.",1:[i.e., exchanged accusations and denials.]
  3,10,"Indeed, those who disbelieve - never will their wealth or their children avail them against Allāh at all. And it is they who are fuel for the Fire."
  3,11,"[Theirs is] like the custom of the people of Pharaoh and those before them. They denied Our signs, so Allāh seized them for their sins. And Allāh is severe in penalty."
  3,12,"Say to those who disbelieve, "